<br>
This was kinda proven today when a lvl 55 or so mage asked if we were meeting at KC or WC for a epic raid in Kithicor, I repeatedly said it was WC because it is right beside Kithicor, the mage then addressed someone else saying he was listening him not &quot;Wyzbe&quot;.  So I called him an idiot because common sense tells you we would meet in WC and I was porting people to WC.<br>
<br>
The guild before I joined this one was great fun, we had a good laugh in guildchat and they were very friendly, but all they ever did was argue alot in the forums and/or during raids, which weren't the most well organised (people not turning up, etc).  So I left.<br>
<br>
So...how should I go about finding a guild, filled with friendly members, who make you feel welcome AND are good at handling problems and organising raids?<br>
<br>
PS  I met someone from a high lvl guild (not uber but lvl 50+), during a Vox raid, where we all died (deaths help people bond), who said his guild was low on wizards and would vouch for me to join once I reach lvl 50.  I asked him a load of questions about how friendly they are, raids, etc and it all sounded good, but is there any way to be sure before I join to find a disaster? <br>
<br>
